  "market_context": "Uptrend on EURUSD 1H chart following a strong impulse move upward; price entered a corrective pullback phase seeking support near prior structure.",
  "key_observation": "Price pulled back to a confluence zone: a bullish order block formed before the last impulse, combined with an inducement low just below it, signaling high-probability buy setup.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified the most recent major swing low as the origin of the current uptrend and marked the last bullish candle before the sharp upward move as the key order block.",
    "Step 2: Analyst observed price retracing into that order block zone and noted a minor internal low (inducement) slightly below the block’s low, which was taken out before the reversal.",
    "Step 3: Analyst confirmed the pullback ended at the confluence of the order block and the inducement zone, where buyers stepped in with strong bullish engulfing candles.",
    "Step 4: Analyst highlighted that the reversal occurred without breaking lower liquidity, indicating institutional absorption and continuation bias."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Valid pullbacks into order blocks are confirmed when price takes out a minor inducement low and reverses sharply—this signals smart money absorption and high-probability continuation entries.",
